President Joe Biden spoke at the National Renewable Energy Laboratory Flatirons Campus in Arvada, Colorado, discussing the importance of addressing climate change and investing in renewable energy. He emphasized the need for everyone to contribute to building a clean energy future and a stronger economy. Biden highlighted the devastating impacts of extreme weather events, such as wildfires and hurricanes, and stressed the urgency of taking action on climate change. He outlined his goals of reducing greenhouse gas emissions and achieving 100% carbon pollution-free power by 2035. Biden also discussed the importance of investing in research and innovation, upgrading the electric grid, and transitioning to electric vehicles. He emphasized that addressing the climate crisis presents an opportunity to create good jobs and industries of the future. Biden concluded by expressing his confidence in the United States' ability to meet these challenges and achieve a sustainable future.